title: SpaceX Launches Science and Supplies To Space Station
summary: NASA and SpaceX have successfully launched the 27th resupply mission to the International Space Station (ISS), carrying over 6,200 pounds of science experiments, crew supplies, and other cargo. The SpaceX Dragon spacecraft was launched by a Falcon 9 rocket on Tuesday from NASA's Kennedy Space Center in Florida and is expected to autonomously dock with the station on Thursday, March 16.

title: Why the Office of Space Commerce should supervise novel commercial space activities
summary: Policymakers are considering establishing an additional supervisory regime to cover novel commercial space activities such as like in-space manufacturing, space tugs, and more. The Office of Space Commerce is the correct choice.

title: NASA Selects Axiom Space for Third Private Astronaut Station Mission
summary: NASA and Axiom Space have signed a mission order for the third private astronaut mission to the International Space Station, targeted to launch no earlier than November 2023 from the agency’s NASA’s Kennedy Space Center in Florida.

title: NASA Selects Firefly Aerospace for Robotic Moon Mission

title: Astranis gets order for a pair of Mexico-focused GEO broadband satellites

title: Viasat deploying ‘zero trust’ cybersecurity across global network
